==English==

===Noun===
'''[[clock]] [[watcher]]'''
# Alternate spelling of [[clock-watcher]]
# A person who is eager for time to pass (e.g., at work or school), especially when faced with an undesirable task.
#: ''The '''clock watcher''' couldn't wait until he got off work at 5 p.m., so he could go home, get some supper and watch TV.''